learnings.details:
Confidential Information includes:

		the ideas, techniques, systems, processes, trade secrets, designs, inventions, methodologies and procedures developed by the College or the Service Provider for the purposes of this Agreement;

		information of the College or any related entity of the College (within the meaning given to the term “related entity” by section 9 of the Corporations Act 2001 (Cth)) relating to its business and business processes, including financial information, accounts, financial records, policies, customer records, employee records, business plans, customer lists and all associated information;

		all reports, proposals, memoranda, drawings, diagrams, statements, accounts and other documents created during the course of the provision of the Services; and

		all copies of any information referred to above, including anything composed and stored digitally embodying or based upon that information,

but does not include any information which:

		is already in the public domain at the time this Agreement is executed or which subsequently falls into the public domain lawfully and through no breach of any duty of confidentiality; or

		is obtained by the Service Provider lawfully and without breaching an obligation of confidence from a source other than the College. **Implication:**  
If GPSA or another organisation takes a policy stance at odds with ACRRM’s approach, ACRRM could view your dual engagement as risky. - This includes methodologies, resources, and business processes【7†source】
